### Lightweight System Monitoring & Real-Time Alert Engine

Titan Sentinel is a robust, headless system monitoring tool built in Python. It tracks critical hardware metrics—CPU, RAM, and Disk—generating real-time alerts and comprehensive post-mortem performance reports.

Designed for Linux environments and servers, it bridges the gap between simple scripts and complex monitoring suites.

## Key Features

* **Precise Monitoring:** High-resolution resource tracking using `psutil`.
* **Smart Alerting:** Integrated Telegram notifications with configurable cooldowns to prevent spam.
* **Data Persistence:** Real-time logging to CSV using context managers (no data loss on crashes).
* **Visual Analytics:** Automatic generation of performance graphs (`system_report.png`) with threshold visualization upon shutdown.
* **Production Ready:** Clean, English-based codebase with professional error handling.

## Setup & Installation

1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/titan-sentinel.git](https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/titan-sentinel.git)
    cd titan-sentinel
    ```

2.  **Install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    pip install psutil matplotlib requests
    ```

3.  **Configure Alerts (Required for notifications):**
    Create two text files in the root directory:
    * `telegram_token.txt`: Paste your Telegram Bot API Token.
    * `telegram_id.txt`: Paste your Telegram Chat ID.

